ing from the s2 hints, which is another completeness gap alongside the `classNamePrefix`/`classNameSuffix` issue I found earlier. The hints guidelines specify that property names should come from tables, and since s2 doesn't have a property table—those are in s3—the inline mentions of `classNamePrefix` and `classNameSuffix` in the processing flow are borderline cases. Still, they do appear as searchable terms in s2 content, so I'll flag this as a minor issue. Let me do one final check to see if there's anything else I've missed. Let me verify the footnote about multibyte characters in the request path—the knowledge file has captured it correctly with the note about ASCII-range characters being acceptable in the request path but resulting in a 404 error if they appear in the mapped Java class name. Now checking the optional section notes. I'm verifying the `requestPattern` property values between the source XML and the description—the XML shows \"/admin//\" and \"/user//\" while the prose mentions \"/sample/admin//\" and \"/sample/user//\", and the knowledge file correctly uses the XML values as the authoritative reference. I also notice the prose says \"nablarch.sample.app1\" but the XML has \"nablarch.sample.apps1\", which the knowledge file properly reflects. So my final finding is just the one minor issue about the s2 hints.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20139,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20139,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8afb1cfe-92cd-44a0-9761-b858197445ae","uuid":"09dfe026-f6b5-4464-aaf4-b3f75dc52846"}
